<br>
One important thing you forgot to mention, on pet classes, both Mages and Necros have items in the game that gives them instant invisb0, this is the ulimate pet control, if things get bad and you can't get your pet off, or he gets away on a misnared mob, you just hit your item and nomore pet.<br>
<br>
On another topic of pets and such, one thing I don't see enough is when pets get a special attack, like backstab, the controllers rarely take advange of this in a group, when I use my rogue pet I always turn taunt off and I act like a rogue myself, I ALWAYS get my pet behind the mob in question, having him follow me, then attacking from behind, then after the fight is over, I send him back out of the water to guard that spot, but since Necros in groups usually are done casting after a few seconds (snare, dot, med is the normal pattern), I figure adding to the damage by having my pet get some backstabs in is always a nice idea.  I only do this when I have room to do it though, don't do it in a place where you can get aggro moving around in the camp, cuz then you could cause problems. <br>
<br>
Anyway, I think in my experience, that for some reason there seems to be more bad mage pet controllers than necros, mb it's just me, just how I've seen it, since mages are much more dependent on pets, they think they should have a pet for EVERY situation, therefore can cause problems.  Anyway, good summary about pets and enchanters <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p><img SRC="http://user.netomia.com/dammned1/sig2.jpg"></br>
